e online application.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Have official foreign documents legalised and translated into Dutch, English, French or German.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "3. Apply", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Will your residence permit expire within 3 months? Then you can apply for extension. You can submit the application online or in writing by post. You can usually apply for extension yourself. Do you have a residence permit as a highly skilled migrant, researcher or student in higher education? Then only your recognised sponsor can submit the application via the Business Portal.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Is your residence permit still valid for more than 3 months? Then you cannot yet submit an application to extend your stay. The IND is then unable to make a proper assessment.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Extend in time, prevent a residence gap", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You should apply for the extension while your residence permit is still valid. Has the validity of your residence permit just expired? In that case, make sure that you submit the application no later than 4 weeks after the expiry of your residence permit. In this way you make sure that the residence permits succeed each other and you will not have a residence gap. If you have a residence gap, it will take longer before you can apply for a permanent residence permit or become a Dutch citizen.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Residence permit expired more than 4 weeks", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Did your residence permit expire more than 4 weeks ago? Then you should apply for extension as soon as possible. You may have a residence gap. Make sure to include a letter in which you explain why you did not apply in time.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Residence permit expired more than 2 years", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Did your residence permit expire 2 or more years ago? Then you can no longer apply for extension. You have to apply for a new residence permit. This means that you may also have to return to your own country to apply for a Provisional Residence Permit (in Dutch: machtiging tot voorlopig verblijf or MVV).", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "4. Pay for application", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You have to pay for the application. To find out how much your application costs, visit our web page Fees: application costs.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "If you submit the application online you pay immediately with iDEAL. Have you applied in writing? Then you will receive a letter explaining how you can pay.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "3. Wait for decision on application", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The IND must take a decision within 90 days. This is called the decision period.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "We can extend the decision period if it takes longer to decide. For example, because the application is not complete. In that case, the IND will send you a letter.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Follow the application in My IND.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "5. Wait for decision on application", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The IND must take a decision within 90 days. This is called the decision period.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "We can extend the decision period if it takes longer to decide. For example, because the application is not complete. In that case, the IND will send you a letter.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Follow the application in My IND.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "6. Decision on application", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The decision will be positive or negative.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Positive decision: your residence permit will be extended.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Negative decision: your residence permit will not be extended. You will receive this decision in a letter. You can object against this decision.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "7. Collect residence permit", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "When the residence permit is ready at an IND desk, you will receive a letter. You must make an appointment to collect it. Make an appointment to collect the residence document.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application forms", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can submit this application online. You must have DigiD with SMS verification and internet banking (iDEAL). Has your residence permit expired? Or were you unable to apply online? Then use the written application form which you sent to the IND by post.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Online application form for extension of your residence permit", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Apply online You need a DigiD", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Written application forms", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit partner", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application residence permit: residence with married or registered partner B07001E (PDF, 437.94 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application residence permit: residence with unmarried partner B07002E (PDF, 479.51 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit minor child", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application residence permit for a minor child to stay with a parent B07004E (PDF, 643.3 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit child born in the Netherlands", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Residence permit application: child born in the Netherlands B07003E (PDF, 335.9 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit for other family members", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for extension of residence permit for residence as a family member or relative (sponsor) 7533 (PDF, 673.11 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for extension of residence permit for residence as family member or relative (foreign national) 7536 (PDF, 644.64 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit temporary humanitarian and permanent humanitarian", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for extension of residence permit for temporary humanitarian and permanent humanitarian (foreign national) 7537 (PDF, 781.78 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit economically inactive long-term third country national from outside the EU", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for extension for residence permit for economically inactive long term third country national form outside the EU (foreign national) 7538 (PDF, 601.88 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit study", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of residence ''study'' (recognised sponsor) Higher education 7504 (PDF, 404.18 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application residence permit for study at secondary education or vocational education (MBO) (393) (recognised sponsor) 7505 (PDF, 372.85 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of residence ''study'' (recognised sponsor) International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme 7506 (PDF, 368.62 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for extension residence permit for study at secondary school or vocational education (393) (foreign national) 7534 (PDF, 233.71 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Extension residence permit work", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of residence of ''paid employment'' (recognised sponsor) 7510 (PDF, 495.65 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of residence ''highly skilled migrant'' (recognised sponsor) 7511 (PDF, 276.09 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of residence of ''scientific researcher'' (recognised sponsor) 7512 (PDF, 538.77 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of residence ''European blue card'' (recognised sponsor) 7513 (PDF, 553.2 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for extension of residence permit for work related purposes of residence (sponsor) 7532 (PDF, 457.79 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for extension of residence permit for work related purposes of residence (foreign national) 7535 (PDF, 456.07 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Aanvraag verlenging gecombineerde vergunning voor verblijf en arbeid (GVVA) (referent) 7047 (PDF, 337.31 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Aanvraag verlenging gecombineerde vergunning voor verblijf en arbeid (GVVA) (vreemdeling) 7048 (PDF, 315.97 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Aanvraag voor een gecombineerde vergunning voor verblijf en arbeid (GVVA) (erkend referent) 7042 (PDF, 167.35 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of stay ''Intra Corporate Transfer'' (Directive 2014/66/EU) (recognised sponsor) 7560 (PDF, 427.67 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of stay ‘Intra Corporate Transfer/Mobile ICT’ (Directive 2014/66/EU) (recognised sponsor) 7563 (PDF, 419.6 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of stay ''Intra Corporate Transfer'' (Directive 2014/66/EU) (sponsor) 7561 (PDF, 465.88 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application for the purpose of stay ‘Intra Corporate Transfer/Mobile ICT’ (Directive 2014/66/EU) (sponsor) 7564 (PDF, 446.21 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Asian catering industry (Aziatische horeca) Did the employee receive a permit after 1 January 2022 for the purpose of residence ''paid employment in Asian Catering Industry''? Then you cannot use this form. You apply for extension using the form Aanvraag verlenging verblijfsvergunning voor arbeidgerelateerde verblijfsdoelen GVVA (referent) 7047 (only available in Dutch).", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Aanvraag verlenging verblijfsvergunning voor het verblijfsdoel ''arbeid in loondienst Aziatische horeca'' (referent) GVVA 7057 (PDF, 477.08 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Apply for a permanent residence permit", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Requirements", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application forms", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "NarrativeText"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.781568+00', 'Regular temporary residence permit extension

Last update: 28 November 2025

You want to extend your regular temporary residence permit (Type I) because it expires within 3 months. Find out what the requirements are and how to apply for extension.

Do you have a temporary asylum residence permit (Type III)? Then visit the web page extend temporary asylum residence permit.

Do you have a residence document verification against EU law for Union citizen family members? Then visit the web page verification against EU law for Union citizen family members.

Requirements

Process and costs

Application forms

See also

Do you have a temporary asylum residence permit (Type III)? Then visit the web page extend temporary asylum residence permit.

Do you have a residence document verification against EU law for Union citizen family members? Then visit the web page verification against EU law for Union citizen family members.

Requirements

You have a valid residence permit that you can still extend. You cannot extend the residence permits for the following residence purposes:

Working Holiday Program/Working Holiday Scheme

Cultural exchange

Au Pair

Stay as a trainee or student on work placement

Orientation year Netherlands

You still meet the requirements for your residence permit. For these requirements visit the web page about the residence permit that you have.

You have a valid passport or another travel document.

Your main residence is in the Netherlands. This means that you live in the Netherlands and spend most of your time there.

You are not a danger to public order or national security.

During the application for the residence permit you have now, you did not give any false information. And you did not withhold information.

Process and costs

These are the steps in the application process for the residence permit:

Show details Hide details

1. Check requirements

A valid provisional residence permit (MVV) is needed for this application

Make sure you meet the requirements.

1. Check requirements

Make sure you meet the requirements.

2. Collect documents

The written application form lists which documents you need. Collect all documents before you apply. You can upload the documents in the online application.

Have official foreign documents legalised and translated into Dutch, English, French or German.

2. Collect documents

The written application form lists which documents you need. Collect all documents before you apply. You can upload the documents in the online application.

Have official foreign documents legalised and translated into Dutch, English, French or German.

3. Apply

Will your residence permit expire within 3 months? Then you can apply for extension. You can submit the application online or in writing by post. You can usually apply for extension yourself. Do you have a residence permit as a highly skilled migrant, researcher or student in higher education? Then only your recognised sponsor can submit the application via the Business Portal.

Is your residence permit still valid for more than 3 months? Then you cannot yet submit an application to extend your stay. The IND is then unable to make a proper assessment.

Extend in time, prevent a residence gap

You should apply for the extension while your residence permit is still valid. Has the validity of your residence permit just expired? In that case, make sure that you submit the application no later than 4 weeks after the expiry of your residence permit. In this way you make sure that the residence permits succeed each other and you will not have a residence gap. If you have a residence gap, it will take longer before you can apply for a permanent residence permit or become a Dutch citizen.

Residence permit expired more than 4 weeks

Did your residence permit expire more than 4 weeks ago? Then you should apply for extension as soon as possible. You may have a residence gap. Make sure to include a letter in which you explain why you did not apply in time.

Residence permit expired more than 2 years

Did your residence permit expire 2 or more years ago? Then you can no longer apply for extension. You have to apply for a new residence permit. This means that you may also have to return to your own country to apply for a Provisional Residence Permit (in Dutch: machtiging tot voorlopig verblijf or MVV).

4. Pay for application

You have to pay for the application. To find out how much your application costs, visit our web page Fees: application costs.

If you submit the application online you pay immediately with iDEAL. Have you applied in writing? Then you will receive a letter explaining how you can pay.

3. Wait for decision on application

The IND must take a decision within 90 days. This is called the decision period.

We can extend the decision period if it takes longer to decide. For example, because the application is not complete. In that case, the IND will send you a letter.

Follow the application in My IND.

5. Wait for decision on application

The IND must take a decision within 90 days. This is called the decision period.

We can extend the decision period if it takes longer to decide. For example, because the application is not complete. In that case, the IND will send you a letter.

Follow the application in My IND.

6. Decision on application

The decision will be positive or negative.

Positive decision: your residence permit will be extended.

Negative decision: your residence permit will not be extended. You will receive this decision in a letter. You can object against this decision.

7. Collect residence permit

When the residence permit is ready at an IND desk, you will receive a letter. You must make an appointment to collect it. Make an appointment to collect the residence document.

Application forms

You can submit this application online. You must have DigiD with SMS verification and internet banking (iDEAL). Has your residence permit expired? Or were you unable to apply online? Then use the written application form which you sent to the IND by post.

