	('fef34bbb-98ff-4f0d-af16-52fbcb684059', 'Becoming a Dutch national through option', 'https://ind.nl/en/dutch-citizenship/becoming-a-dutch-national-through-option', '{"category": "dutch-citizenship", "elements": [{"text": "Becoming a Dutch national through option", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Last update: 20 February 2026", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "You have a strong bond with the Netherlands. You therefore want to apply for Dutch nationality more quickly through option. Read what the requirements are and how you apply for option.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Requirements", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "After a positive decision", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Requirements", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The option procedure is a quick way to become a Dutch citizen . You can apply for option at your municipality with an option declaration.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Persons who can apply for option", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Not everyone can obtain Dutch nationality through option. You can only apply for option if one of the following situations applies to you:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Show details Hide details", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You were born in the Kingdom of the Netherlands", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You were born in the Kingdom of the Netherlands and have always lived in the Kingdom. You have now reached the age of majority and have a valid residence permit.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You were born without citizenship (stateless) in the Kingdom of the Netherlands. You have live in the Kingdom for at least 3 consecutive years with a valid residence permit.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are younger than 21 years old and were born without citizenship (stateless) in the Kingdom of the Netherlands. You cannot reasonably obtain another nationality. Immediately before your option declaration, you had your main residence in the Netherlands for at least 5 consecutive years. You have a permanent main residence if you meet all 3 of the following points:", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have actually lived in the Kingdom for at least 5 consecutive years.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You and your parents have always actively participated in the departure process.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You and your parents have always remained in the attention of the Dutch State.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are recognised by or are under the authority of a Dutch person", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You are a minor and acknowledged by a Dutch citizen. You have not become Dutch through the acknowledgement. This Dutch citizen has cared for you and raised you for at least 3 years without interruption on the date of your option declaration.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are a minor and have been under the joint authority of a non-Dutch parent and a Dutch parent since birth. Dutch law has determined that your parents have joint authority over you, or this has been ruled by a judge in the Netherlands. You can apply for option if you meet the following requirements:", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Since the parental authority was determined, the Dutch parent has cared for you and raised you for at least 3 years without interruption.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You do not live in the country of which you are a national.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have been living in the Netherlands for a long time", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You have lived in the Kingdom of the Netherlands since the day you turned 4 years old. You have always had a valid residence permit. You have now reached the age of majority.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have been living in the Kingdom of the Netherlands for at least 15 consecutive years with a valid residence permit and you have been the married or registered partner of a Dutch citizen for at least 3 years.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have lived in the Kingdom of the Netherlands for at least 15 consecutive years with a valid residence permit. You are now 65 years or older.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You were born before 1 January 1985 from or adopted by a Dutch mother, or you are the child of this person", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You were born to a Dutch mother before 1 January 1985. Your father did not have Dutch nationality at the time of your birth.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "A woman who had Dutch nationality at the time adopted you before 1 January 1985. You were a minor at the time. A court in the Kingdom of the Netherlands pronounced the adoption.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are a child of a person who was born before 1 January 1985 from or adopted by a Dutch mother. The father of this person did not have Dutch nationality at the time of birth. You are a child of this person by birth, adoption, acknowledgement or court ruling. Contact your municipality to find out whether you can indeed become Dutch through the option.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You had Dutch nationality before (former Dutch citizen)", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You have lost your Dutch nationality because you married a non-Dutch man before 1 January 1985. You and your husband are now divorced, or your husband has died. You make the option declaration within 1 year after the end of your marriage. You do not need to live in the Kingdom for this.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are a former Dutch citizen. You have been living in the Kingdom of the Netherlands for at least 1 year with a valid permanent residence permit or a temporary residence permit with a non-temporary purpose of residence. If you previously lost your Dutch nationality because you did not renounce your other nationality, you cannot apply for option.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are a former Dutch citizen because you automatically lost your Dutch nationality. As a result, you are no longer a citizen of the European Union (EU). The consequences of the loss of your Union citizenship were disproportionate at that time. Disproportionate means that the consequences of this loss are so heavy that it should not have happened. You must prove that you used your rights as a citizen of the Union 6 months before the loss or that you would have used your rights as a citizen of the Union in the 6 months after the loss. It concerns, for example:", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "the ability to travel freely within the EU", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "the ability to give meaning to your family life", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "the ability to practice your profession", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "the ability to continue your studies", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "what is best for your children under 18 living in the EU.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Additional requirements for option", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "In addition, the following requirements apply when applying for option:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You prove your identity and nationality with valid documents, for example, a passport and birth certificate.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You pose no danger to public order or the national security of the Kingdom.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You make the Declaration of Solidarity (in Dutch: Verklaring van verbondenheid) during the naturalisation ceremony. With the Declaration of Solidarity, you show that you know that the laws of the Kingdom of the Netherlands also apply to you.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Only if you have lived in the Kingdom since the day you turned 4 years old: you must renounce the nationality you currently have. Before applying for option, read whether you have to renounce your nationality and what this means.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Option and children", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Your child under the age of 18 can apply for Dutch nationality together with you. You fill this in on the option declaration. Your child must live in the Netherlands at the time of the application with a valid residence permit. Children aged 16 and 17 must be present when applying. They must state that they agree with the application. Minor children do not have to renounce their other nationality.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Post-naturalisation of a child", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Was your child born during your procedure? Procedure is the time between the application and the decision that you will be granted Dutch nationality. Then you should apply for post-naturalisation for your child. Your child must live in the Kingdom of the Netherlands with a valid residence permit for a non-temporary residence purpose. If you are applying for post-naturalisation within 1 year after you have been granted Dutch nationality, then the application for your child is free of charge.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The application procedure consists of the following steps:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Show details Hide details", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "1. Check requirements", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "A valid provisional residence permit (MVV) is needed for this application", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Make sure you meet the requirements.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "1. Check requirements", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Make sure you meet the requirements.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "2. Collect documents", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You use documents to show that you meet the requirements for naturalisation. You should have official foreign documents legalised and translated into Dutch, English, French or German. If your foreign documents are already registered in the Personal Records Database (BRP), you do not need to request the documents again abroad.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You need the following documents:", "type": "Narrativ