	('468730c5-576d-4134-98e3-0f73df1c9fbe', 'Our work areas', 'https://ind.nl/en/about-us', '{"category": "about-us", "elements": [{"text": "Our work areas", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "At the IND, we decide on all applications by everyone who would like to live in the Netherlands. They may be applying for asylum or want to be here for family, to work or study in the Netherlands. And we are there for everyone who has already been living here from some time and would like to apply for Dutch citizenship.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Immigration and naturalisation", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "At the IND, we assess the applications of everyone who would like to stay in the Netherlands. They may be seeking asylum, or perhaps they would like to live with their family, or to work of study in the Netherlands. And we also help everyone who has already been living here for some time and would like to become a Dutch citizen.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "More about us", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "What we do", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Asylum", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Every year, many people apply for asylum in the Netherlands because they are not safe in their own country. We assess these applications. When we do this, we always look at someone’s personal story.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Economy", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The Netherlands wants to clear the way for international talent. At the IND we therefore consider every application from people wishing to come here to work or study.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Naturalisation", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Some people who have been living in the Netherlands for a long time feel Dutch. They can apply for Dutch nationality. Every year, we assess tens of thousands of these applications.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Family", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Every year, many people apply for a partner, child, or other family member to come to the Netherlands. We assess whether these relatives are allowed to stay in the Netherlands.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Stories about our work", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Our employees’ stories", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Whoever works for the IND, works for people and society. Find out more about our areas of expertise, experience and the choices we face every day.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Our clients’ stories", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "How do people come into contact with the IND? What was their experience? And how do they look back on their application for asylum or naturalisation? Read their stories.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Backgroundarticles", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Would you like to know more? We regularly write articles with more information about everything to do with our work areas of asylum, the economy, family and naturalization.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "More about us", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Statistics and publications", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "This page contains all recent publications and statistics about immigration and naturalisation.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Working at the IND", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "What can you do for us? Read more about working for the IND. And while you are here, why not check our latest vacancies.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Press and information", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Want to know more about the IND? Read our files or make an appointment for a presentation on location.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Go quickly to", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "We are active on social media", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Facebook", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Instagram", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "LinkedIn", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "YouTube", "type": "UncategorizedText"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.738728+00', 'Our work areas

At the IND, we decide on all applications by everyone who would like to live in the Netherlands. They may be applying for asylum or want to be here for family, to work or study in the Netherlands. And we are there for everyone who has already been living here from some time and would like to apply for Dutch citizenship.

Immigration and naturalisation

At the IND, we assess the applications of everyone who would like to stay in the Netherlands. They may be seeking asylum, or perhaps they would like to live with their family, or to work of study in the Netherlands. And we also help everyone who has already been living here for some time and would like to become a Dutch citizen.

More about us

What we do

Asylum

Every year, many people apply for asylum in the Netherlands because they are not safe in their own country. We assess these applications. When we do this, we always look at someone’s personal story.

Economy

The Netherlands wants to clear the way for international talent. At the IND we therefore consider every application from people wishing to come here to work or study.

Naturalisation

Some people who have been living in the Netherlands for a long time feel Dutch. They can apply for Dutch nationality. Every year, we assess tens of thousands of these applications.

Family

Every year, many people apply for a partner, child, or other family member to come to the Netherlands. We assess whether these relatives are allowed to stay in the Netherlands.

Stories about our work

Our employees’ stories

Whoever works for the IND, works for people and society. Find out more about our areas of expertise, experience and the choices we face every day.

Our clients’ stories

How do people come into contact with the IND? What was their experience? And how do they look back on their application for asylum or naturalisation? Read their stories.

Backgroundarticles

Would you like to know more? We regularly write articles with more information about everything to do with our work areas of asylum, the economy, family and naturalization.

More about us

Statistics and publications

This page contains all recent publications and statistics about immigration and naturalisation.

Working at the IND

What can you do for us? Read more about working for the IND. And while you are here, why not check our latest vacancies.

Press and information

Want to know more about the IND? Read our files or make an appointment for a presentation on location.

Go quickly to

We are active on social media

Facebook

Instagram

LinkedIn

YouTube'),
