Do you want to learn more about our work and our results? Then have a look at our statistics and publications. And those of other organisations in the migration system.

Asylum Trends

Here, you can find our monthly report about asylum applications in the Netherlands and Europe..

The IND in figures

Here you will find the publication of the most important figures of the IND.

Migration Radar

Do you want to know everything about migration flows of asylum seekers to Europe and the Netherlands? And the latest developments in the field of (asylum) migration? Find out more here.

Annual IND reports

Every year we publish an annual report. These are interesting if you are curious about our results and developments in recent years.

Trend analyses, policy monitors and evaluations

The IND makes trend analyses, policy monitors and evaluations of asylum and migration. You can find them here.

Complaints handling

On this page we give insight how the IND handles complaints.

Work instructions and country-specific information

In addition to laws and policies we also use other information to process applications. For example work instructions. Are you curious? Then have a look at these public documents. In them, you can find an explanation about policies and case law – or instructions for an application process. Or the current situation in a country of origin (only in Dutch available).

Work instructions

Information messages

Country-specific information

Protocols (BMA protocol)

More about us

Press and information

Current topics, facts, and background information are available on the Press and information page.

Working for the IND

day after day you help people faced with major events in their lives when you are a member of the IND staff. These people need us. And we need you.

Articles about our work

We regularly post background articles where you can find more information about our organisation and what we mean for society.

More statistics and publications'),
