	('a81af232-a137-4043-ae0c-db1bad6028f9', 'My IND', 'https://ind.nl/en/my-ind', '{"category": "my-ind", "elements": [{"text": "My IND", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "My IND is an online service from the IND. In My IND you can log in to see your personal details and the status of your application.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Log in", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "To use My IND you have to log in using DigiD. DigiD is explained in different languages (Dutch, English, French, Arabic and Tigrinya).", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Go to My IND", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Track your application on My IND", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Watch the video below for an instruction.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "00:00", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "00:00", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Information in My IND", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "My IND has the following subjects:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Applications", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can check the status of your application and how long it may take for the IND to decide. After you receive a decision, your application will remain visible for 28 days. Each application has a legal or reasonable decision period. The IND can use this entire period to process your application. Has the decision period for your application not yet expired? Then your application is still being processed.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Follow-up options", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Here you see an overview of other applications you can make in your situation. You only see a follow up application when you can submit that application. For example, you see the option for extension only from 3 months before your residence permit expires.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Residence permit", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Here you see which residence permit you have. And the information that is printed on the residence document.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Personal details", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Here you see your personal details as known to the IND. Some details you can change yourself. Other details you will have to get changed at the municipality.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Family members", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Are you a sponsor for a family member? Then you can also view your family member''s information. Would you like to see your child''s information? And is your child younger than 12 years old? Then log in with your own DigiD. You will not see any data if you use your child''s DigiD.", "type": "NarrativeText"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.738728+00', 'My IND

My IND is an online service from the IND. In My IND you can log in to see your personal details and the status of your application.

Log in

To use My IND you have to log in using DigiD. DigiD is explained in different languages (Dutch, English, French, Arabic and Tigrinya).

Go to My IND

Track your application on My IND

Watch the video below for an instruction.

00:00

00:00

Information in My IND

My IND has the following subjects:

Applications

You can check the status of your application and how long it may take for the IND to decide. After you receive a decision, your application will remain visible for 28 days. Each application has a legal or reasonable decision period. The IND can use this entire period to process your application. Has the decision period for your application not yet expired? Then your application is still being processed.

Follow-up options

Here you see an overview of other applications you can make in your situation. You only see a follow up application when you can submit that application. For example, you see the option for extension only from 3 months before your residence permit expires.

Residence permit

Here you see which residence permit you have. And the information that is printed on the residence document.

Personal details

Here you see your personal details as known to the IND. Some details you can change yourself. Other details you will have to get changed at the municipality.

Family members

Are you a sponsor for a family member? Then you can also view your family member''s information. Would you like to see your child''s information? And is your child younger than 12 years old? Then log in with your own DigiD. You will not see any data if you use your child''s DigiD.'),
	('8247fa7e-f9aa-458f-9329-caa42e9caaca', 'Business Portal', 'https://ind.nl/en/business-portal', '{"category": "business-portal", "elements": [{"text": "Business Portal", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "In the Business Portal, business customers of the IND can submit applications. Find out which services are available in the Business Portal and what you need to log in.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Log in", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Login Business Portal", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "eHerkenning required", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You need eHerkenning level 3 (EH3) or higher to log in to the Business Portal. Read how to apply at eHerkenning.nl. After you apply, it may take a few days to log in.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Authorisation", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you want another company or organisation (intermediary) to use the Business Portal on behalf of you? This is possible with a chain authorisation. You or your intermediary applies for the chain authorisation to the supplier of eHerkenning. The manager of eHerkenning within your organisation can help you with this. Read more about chain authorisation at eHerkenning.nl.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Chain authorisation mandatory since 4 November 2024", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Since 4 November 2024 intermediaries can only log in with a chain authorisation. An authorisation by the IND is no longer valid. Read our frequently asked questions on eHerkenning and authorisations for the Business Portal.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Services Business Portal", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The Business Portal is currently only available for recognised sponsors and their authorised intermediaries. The following services are available:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "submit applications; You only see the applications that you have to submit for your employees. Other applications, like a permanent residence permit, can only be submitted by your employee. Your employees themselves can see which applications they can submit in their situations in My IND.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "view the status of your submitted applications", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "register or de-register an employee;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "report a change in the situation of an employee or recognised sponsor", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "view account information;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "access to file documents.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The IND refreshes the information in the portal once a day.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Reporting technical issues", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you have login problems or are there technical issues in the Business Portal? First check if these problems are not caused by your Internet provider or supplier of your eHerkenning? Is this not the issue? Then see if the solution to your problem can be found in frequently asked questions and answers about the Business Portal.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Do you continue to have technical problems? Please send an e-mail to Servicedesk Business Portal with the following information:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "screenshot of the error which also shows the internet address;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Chamber of Commerce (Kamer van Koophandel or KVK) number;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "date and exact time of the error;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "short description of the problem or technical issue.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Upon receipt, the IND will assess your report.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Apply for recognition as a sponsor", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "​More information", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Frequently asked questions", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Information overview Working in the Netherlands", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Required amounts income requirements", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Securely emailing additional documents", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Obligations sponsor and recognised sponsor", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Business Newsletter for recognised sponsors employment", "type": "ListItem"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.738728+00', 'Business Portal

In the Business Portal, business customers of the IND can submit applications. Find out which services are available in the Business Portal and what you need to log in.

Log in

Login Business Portal

eHerkenning required

You need eHerkenning level 3 (EH3) or higher to log in to the Business Portal. Read how to apply at eHerkenning.nl. After you apply, it may take a few days to log in.

Authorisation

Do you want another company or organisation (intermediary) to use the Business Portal on behalf of you? This is possible with a chain authorisation. You or your intermediary applies for the chain authorisation to the supplier of eHerkenning. The manager of eHerkenning within your organisation can help you with this. Read more about chain authorisation at eHerkenning.nl.

Chain authorisation mandatory since 4 November 2024

Since 4 November 2024 intermediaries can only log in with a chain authorisation. An authorisation by the IND is no longer valid. Read our frequently asked questions on eHerkenning and authorisations for the Business Portal.

Services Business Portal

The Business Portal is currently only available for recognised sponsors and their authorised intermediaries. The following services are available:

submit applications; You only see the applications that you have to submit for your employees. Other applications, like a permanent residence permit, can only be submitted by your employee. Your employees themselves can see which applications they can submit in their situations in My IND.

view the status of your submitted applications

register or de-register an employee;

report a change in the situation of an employee or recognised sponsor

view account information;

access to file documents.

The IND refreshes the information in the portal once a day.

Reporting technical issues

Do you have login problems or are there technical issues in the Business Portal? First check if these problems are not caused by your Internet provider or supplier of your eHerkenning? Is this not the issue? Then see if the solution to your problem can be found in frequently asked questions and answers about the Business Portal.

Do you continue to have technical problems? Please send an e-mail to Servicedesk Business Portal with the following information:

screenshot of the error which also shows the internet address;

Chamber of Commerce (Kamer van Koophandel or KVK) number;

date and exact time of the error;

short description of the problem or technical issue.

Upon receipt, the IND will assess your report.

See also

Apply for recognition as a sponsor

​More information

Frequently asked questions

Information overview Working in the Netherlands

Required amounts income requirements

Securely emailing additional documents

Obligations sponsor and recognised sponsor

Business Newsletter for recognised sponsors employment'),
	('2cc5d5ee-ed01-4b93-9829-220a18ca89c2', 'Solicitor Portal', 'https://ind.nl/en/solicitor-portal', '{"category": "solicitor-portal", "elements": [{"text": "Solicitor Portal", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Last update: 3 June 2025", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "In the Solicitor Portal, you can view and submit documents for your clients’ ongoing asylum cases. Find out which services are available in the Solicitor Portal and what you need to log in.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "To get access to the Solicitor Portal, you need a Solicitor Information Card (in Dutch: advocatenpas) from The Netherlands Bar (Nederlandse orde van advocaten or NOvA).", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Login Solicitor Portal", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Services Solicitor Portal", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The following services are available in the Solicitor Portal:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Access to the customer and case data of ongoing asylum cases. This applies to the following:", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Temporary residence permit asylum", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Asylum procedure unaccompanied minor foreign nationals (UAMs)", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Repeat Asylum Application", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Side influx after appeal to Court General Asylum Procedure", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Side influx after appeal to Court Extended Asylum Procedure", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "View the status of the asylum case", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Access to documents of the ongoing asylum case, such as interviews, letters, intentions, decisions", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Access to cases of family members; you are an authorized representative for this part of the ongoing asylum case", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Submit documents in the case", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Corrections and additions", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Viewpoints", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Additional documents, such as a request for postponement and vacation notices", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The IND refreshes the information in the portal once a day.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Missing cases and documents", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Are you missing ongoing asylum cases in your overview or are documents missing from a specific case? Please send us an email that has at least the following information:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Case number. Don''t you have a case number? Please mention your V-number.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The documents that are missing.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "All documents are carefully linked to your account based on your BAR number. Do you see a case or document that is not for you or your client? Please send us an email.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Reporting technical issues", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you have login problems or are there technical issues in the Solicitor Portal? First check if these problems are not caused by your Internet provider. Is this not the issue? Then see if the solution to your problem can be found in frequently asked questions and answers about the Solicitor Portal.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Do you continue to have technical problems? Please send us an email with the following information:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Screenshot of the error;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Date and exact time of the error;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Short description of the problem or technical issue.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Upon receipt, the IND will assess your report.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Manual", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you want to know how the Solicitor''s Portal works or do you need help with logging in? Read the manual (only available in Dutch).", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "More information", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Frequently asked questions and answers Solicitor Portal", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Handleiding Portaal voor Advocaten (in Dutch only)", "type": "ListItem"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.738728+00', 'Solicitor Portal

Last update: 3 June 2025

In the Solicitor Portal, you can view and submit documents for your clients’ ongoing asylum cases. Find out which services are available in the Solicitor Portal and what you need to log in.

To get access to the Solicitor Portal, you need a Solicitor Information Card (in Dutch: advocatenpas) from The Netherlands Bar (Nederlandse orde van advocaten or NOvA).

Login Solicitor Portal

Services Solicitor Portal

The following services are available in the Solicitor Portal:

Access to the customer and case data of ongoing asylum cases. This applies to the following:

Temporary residence permit asylum

Asylum procedure unaccompanied minor foreign nationals (UAMs)

Repeat Asylum Application

Side influx after appeal to Court General Asylum Procedure

Side influx after appeal to Court Extended Asylum Procedure

View the status of the asylum case

Access to documents of the ongoing asylum case, such as interviews, letters, intentions, decisions

Access to cases of family members; you are an authorized representative for this part of the ongoing asylum case

Submit documents in the case

Corrections and additions

Viewpoints

Additional documents, such as a request for postponement and vacation notices

The IND refreshes the information in the portal once a day.

Missing cases and documents

Are you missing ongoing asylum cases in your overview or are documents missing from a specific case? Please send us an email that has at least the following information:

Case number. Don''t you have a case number? Please mention your V-number.

The documents that are missing.

All documents are carefully linked to your account based on your BAR number. Do you see a case or document that is not for you or your client? Please send us an email.

Reporting technical issues

Do you have login problems or are there technical issues in the Solicitor Portal? First check if these problems are not caused by your Internet provider. Is this not the issue? Then see if the solution to your problem can be found in frequently asked questions and answers about the Solicitor Portal.

Do you continue to have technical problems? Please send us an email with the following information:

Screenshot of the error;

Date and exact time of the error;

Short description of the problem or technical issue.

Upon receipt, the IND will assess your report.

Manual

Do you want to know how the Solicitor''s Portal works or do you need help with logging in? Read the manual (only available in Dutch).

More information

Frequently asked questions and answers Solicitor Portal

Handleiding Portaal voor Advocaten (in Dutch only)'),
	('a75eec0f-4b92-41bf-807d-f0c076a2606e', 'Municipality Portal', 'https://ind.nl/en/municipality-portal', '{"category": "municipality-portal", "elements": [{"text": "Municipality Portal", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Welcome to this IND Portal for municipalities. On this page you can gain access to a secure environment of the IND. Municipality employees can submit and manage applications to the IND quickly and easily.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Log in", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Login Municipality Portal", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "eHerkenning required", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You need eHerkenning level 3 (EH3) or higher to log in to the Municipality Portal. Read how to apply at eHerkenning.nl. After you apply, it may take a few days to log in.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Authorisation", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you want another company or organisation (intermediary) to use the Municipality Portal on behalf of you? This is possible with a chain authorisation. You or your intermediary applies for the chain authorisation to the supplier of eHerkenning. The manager of eHerkenning within your organisation can help you with this. Read more about chain authorisation at eHerkenning.nl.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "More information", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "For more information about the Municipality Portal, please visit the Dutch version of this webpage (or by clicking on the Dutch flag in the upper right corner).", "type": "NarrativeText"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.738728+00', 'Municipality Portal

Welcome to this IND Portal for municipalities. On this page you can gain access to a secure environment of the IND. Municipality employees can submit and manage applications to the IND quickly and easily.

