	('be8e47de-517b-4b4b-bbaf-5d2dbbd03a3f', 'Object decision on Schengen or transit visa', 'https://ind.nl/en/short-stay/object-decision-on-schengen-or-transit-visa', '{"category": "short-stay", "elements": [{"text": "Object decision on Schengen or transit visa", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Last update: 9 October 2025", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "You applied for a short-stay visa or transit visa. Your application has been rejected and you do not agree with that decision. Find out how you can object.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Object in the right country", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can only object to the IND if the Netherlands has decided on your application. Did another country take the decision? Then you must object in that country.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "When to object", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Who can object", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Object in the right country", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can only object to the IND if the Netherlands has decided on your application. Did another country take the decision? Then you must object in that country.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "When to object", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You applied to a Dutch representation for a Schengen visa for a short stay in the Netherlands, for example for business, a holiday, or a family visit. Or you applied there for a transit visa for a transit in the Netherlands. Your visa application has been rejected. Or your visa has been revoked or annulled. Do you disagree with the decision? Then you can object. You must object within 4 weeks. The 4-week period starts 1 day after the decision has been announced.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Processing objections now takes longer", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Read when to expect a decision on your objection.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Who can object", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can object yourself, or someone else can object for you. These people can object for you.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Your legal representative. This is a parent, guardian, or someone else who manages your affairs.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "A lawyer.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "A specially authorised person. This is someone who you give permission to object on your behalf. You must give this person written permission (authorisation). Use this form:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Authorisation Objection Visa Decision 4534 (PDF, 126.93 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Assistance when objecting", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can ask someone who provides legal or other assistance to help you object. Find out more about legal or other assistance providers from the Juridisch Loket (legal aid and advice centre).", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "These are the steps in the objection process:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Show details Hide details", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "1. Check objection period", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Check the date before which you must object. You have 4 weeks’ time to object. The 4-week period starts 1 day after the decision has been announced.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "2. Collect documents", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Perhaps your Schengen visa application was incomplete. Please collect the missing documents. On Netherlandsworldwide.nl you will find a checklist of documents you need when applying for a visa for the Netherlands.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Is someone else objecting on your behalf? Then use the following authorisation along with a copy of your passport:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Authorisation Objection Visa Decision 4534 (PDF, 126.93 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Have official foreign documents translated into Dutch, English, French or German.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "3. Objecting", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can object in writing or online.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Objecting online by sponsor", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Was the short-stay visa intended for visiting family or friends? Then your sponsor can submit an objection online for you. The sponsor is the person who has invited you. The sponsor uses the online objection form (in Dutch).", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Was the visa applied for for another reason? In that case, it is only possible to submit a written objection.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Written objection", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Please send a written objection to the IND. You must do this in a letter or by emailing securely. Your letter must be written in Dutch, English, German or French.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Content of written objection", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Your written objection must at least contain this information:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "your name, date of birth and address.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "the date.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "why you think the decision is incorrect.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "your signature.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "a copy of the decision.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Send supporting documents.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Does it concern a visa for family or friends? Then please send the questionnaire Vragenlijst Visumaanvraag along with your objection. Do this for each visa applicant of 12 years and older. Are you objecting on behalf of a child below the age of 12 who is travelling without parents? Then send the Vragenlijst Visumaanvraag along as well. The Vragenlijst Visumaanvraag is only available in Dutch.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You can send the completed forms together with all the supporting documents to the IND. Are you not able to send the questionnaire together with the objection? Then forward it as soon as possible.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Postal address", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Send your written objection to:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "IND Visadienst Postbus 2 9560 AA Ter Apel", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Securely email", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can also securely email your objection and documents:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Mention the case number in the subject of your email.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your written objection is signed with a signature.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The documents should each be up to 10 MB. Together your documents should be up to 20 MB per email. Are your documents together larger than 20 MB? Please send an extra email with the other documents.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Read more about emailing securely with Zivver.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Start mailing securely", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Uploading additional digital documents", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you wish to send additional document to the IND? And is your objection still in progress with the IND? If you have a DigiD account, uploading documents is quick and easy.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Do you not have DigiD? You can also securely email your additional documents.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "4. Costs of objection", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Objecting is free of charge.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "5. Wait for decision on objection", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The IND must take a decision within a 6-week decision period. We can extend this by another 6 weeks. Did the IND receive your objection on time? Then the decision period starts on the first day after the final date on which you could submit your objection. Sending your objection earlier does not change that.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Processing objections now takes longer", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "At the moment, an appeal can take 6 months to pr