	('294f38ae-131a-44e0-8df5-8700160145fa', 'Residence with your minor Dutch child (Chavez)', 'https://ind.nl/en/residence-permits/family-and-partner/residence-with-your-minor-dutch-child-chavez', '{"category": "residence-permits/family-and-partner", "elements": [{"text": "Residence with your minor Dutch child (Chavez)", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Last update: 18 September 2025", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "In order to live with a Dutch child under 18, as a caring parent, (half)brother or (half)sister, you need a residence document. Read what the conditions are and how you can apply for the document.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Requirements, process and costs", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application forms", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "The residence document", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Requirements, process and costs", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The process for the application for the residence document consists of these steps:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Show details Hide details", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "1. Check requirements", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "These requirements apply to you:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Proof of identity and nationality", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You have a valid passport or identity card. Or you can show your identity and nationality with other documents.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Family ties", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You are the parent of a minor Dutch child (your child is under 18 years old). You may also be the step-parent, foster parent or NIDOS-appointed foster parent of the child. Your child has already been born.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Living together", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The minor Dutch child already lives in the Netherlands or is going to live with you in the Netherlands.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Dependence", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The minor Dutch child is heavily dependent on you. This also means that if you do not obtain a residence document, your child will have no choice but to leave the European Union (EU) together with you.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You care for your child and are responsible for their upbringing. You may do so together with your child’s other parent. Do you only help out with your child’s care and upbringing every now and then? This is usually not sufficient.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Nationality and right of residence", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You do not have the nationality of a European Union (EU) or EEA Member State or Switzerland. Nor do you have lawful residence in the Netherlands, another EU/EEA Member State or Switzerland.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "No danger to public order or national safety", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You are not a danger to public order or national safety. Everyone over the age of 12 must completely fill in an Appendix Antecedents Certificate and enclose it with the application. In this certificate you indicate whether you have ever committed an offence or crime.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Additional requirements for (half)brother or (half)sister of the minor Dutch child", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you have another non-Dutch child under 18 (a minor)? And this is a (half)brother or (half)sister of your Dutch child under 18? Then the following requirements also apply:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "The (half)brother or (half)sister is going to live with you and your Dutch child under 18 in the Netherlands.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The (half)brother or (half)sister is part of your family.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The (half)brother or (half)sister is your child. This can be your biological child or your child by law.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have parental authority of the (half)brother or (half)sister. Read more about parental responsibility on Rijksoverheid.nl.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Is there a parent of the (half)brother or (half)sister who is staying behind in the country of origin? And does that parent have authority? Then that parent needs to give permission for the departure of the (half)brother or (half)sister to the Netherlands. Sometimes permission is also required from the government of the country of origin. For example, if this is laid down by law in the country of origin. Or, if the parents or legal representatives have died or cannot be found.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You take care of the (half)brother or (half)sister and are responsible for their upbringing.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "One of the following situations applies to you:", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have a residence permit EU as a caring parent of a Dutch child under 18.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have a facilitation visa. With this visa, you may apply in the Netherlands as a caring parent of a Dutch child under 18.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have another valid Dutch residence permit", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The (half)brother or (half)sister strongly depends on you. This means that if the (half)brother or (half)sister does not get a residence document, you and your Dutch child under 18 have no choice but to leave the European Union (EU) together with the (half)brother or (half)sister.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "2. Collect documents", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Would you like to know which documents you need to submit the application? Then answer a few questions and get your document overview.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Go to questions for your document overview", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Have official foreign documents legalised and translated into Dutch, English, French or German.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "3. Travel to the Netherlands", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Check if you need free Schengen visa facilitation to travel to the Netherlands. Go to Vi