	('e3c434c4-79d2-4637-9085-bc586d2cdcd3', 'Apply for recognition as sponsor', 'https://ind.nl/en/residence-permits/work/apply-for-recognition-as-sponsor', '{"category": "residence-permits/work", "elements": [{"text": "Apply for recognition as sponsor", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Last update: 8 July 2025", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "You would like to apply for recognition as a sponsor. A recognised sponsor is a company, school or organisation that has an interest in the arrival of a third-country national. Watch the video, read what the requirements are and how to apply for recognition.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Video: How do I apply for recognition as a sponsor?", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Categories of recognition as sponsor", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Recognition is sometimes mandatory", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Advantages of recognition as sponsor", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Obligations as recognised sponsor", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Requirements", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application form", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Video: How do I apply for recognition as a sponsor?", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "00:00", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "00:00", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Categories of recognition as sponsor", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can apply for recognition as a sponsor for the following 4 categories.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Study: applications for residence permits for the purpose of study.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Exchange: applications for residence permits for the purpose of au pair and cultural exchange.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Research: applications for residence permits for the purpose of research under Directive (EU) 2016/801.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Work: applications for residence permits for the purpose of work as a highly-skilled migrant, work in paid employment, seasonal labour, gaining work experience, intra-corporate transfer or residence as the holder of a European Blue Card.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Do you want to become a recognised sponsor for more than one category? In that case you must apply separately for each recognition category.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Do you want to apply for recognition for each business unit or faculty? In that case you have to apply for recognition for each branch or business unit.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Recognition is sometimes mandatory", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Recognition is mandatory if you want to apply for these residence purposes as a company, educational institution or organisation.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Au pair", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Exchange", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Study", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Highly-skilled migrant", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Researchers under Directive (EU) 2016/801", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "An exception applies to highly-skilled migrants and researchers with Turkish nationality.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "And recognition is not mandatory, but it is possible for these residence purposes.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Regular work in paid employment", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Seasonal work", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Gaining work experience", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Intra-company transfer", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Holder of a European Blue Card", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "For these residence purposes, you can choose whether or not to have your organisation recognised as a sponsor.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Advantages of recognition as sponsor", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Recognition as a sponsor has several advantages.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "The IND processes your applications faster. The IND tries to decide on an application within 2 weeks. In some cases the target period is 7 weeks, for example if a work permit (in Dutch: tewerkstellingsvergunning) is needed.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You need to enclose fewer supporting documents with the application.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You can apply for residence permits online via the Business Portal.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are not obligated to submit a minimum or maximum number of applications per year.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Obligations as recognised sponsor", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "If you are recognised as a sponsor, then you will have several legal obligations. See the obligations of a sponsor and recognised sponsor.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Requirements", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "There are general requirements for applying for recognition as a sponsor that apply to all categories. In addition, extra requirements also apply to the categories research, study and exchange.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "General conditions in applying for recognition as a sponsor", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The following conditions apply to your organisation:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Your organisation is registered in the Commercial Register in the Netherlands (in Dutch: Handelsregister). This is not necessary if not required under the Commercial Register Act 2007 (Hrw 2007).", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The continuity and solvency of your organisation is sufficiently guaranteed.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your organisation is not insolvent or has not been granted suspension of payment.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your organisation, directors and officers and other natural persons and legal entities involved in your organisation are reliable.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your organisation complies with the Code of Conduct that applies to your organisation. Does your organisation carry out activities such as assigning personnel for payment? Then your organisation must be listed in the register of the Labour Standards Foundation (SNA). Has the registration of your organisation in the register of the SNA been terminated? But are you still engaged providing employees or payrolling. Then you must report the termination.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Show details Hide details", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Continuity and solvency of the organisation", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Continuity means that your organisation can comply with all financial obligations in the longer term. Solvency is that the organisation has the financial health to deal with financial setbacks.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Advice from the Netherlands Enterprise Agency (RVO)", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The IND can ask the Netherlands Enterprise Agency (in Dutch: Rijksdienst voor Ondernemend Nederland or RVO) for advice on the continuity and solvency of businesses. For start-up businesses the RVO uses a point system to assess this. A maximum of 100 points can be obtained. You need at least 50 points for positive advice.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Sections of the point system", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "1. Registration with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce (in Dutch: Kamer van Koophandel or KvK)", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Is the organisation registered?", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Have there been any changes in partners, shareholders or control since the application date?", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Has there been a takeover, suspension of payment or insolvency of the organisation or of its owners/directors and officers?", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "2. Business Plan", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Market potential", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Description of unique characteristics of the product or service.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Qualitative and quantitative analyses of the market, focusing on one’s own business environment.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Organisation", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Clear and appropriate organisational structure.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The right competencies in relation to entrepreneurship, management and subject matter.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Financing", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The organisation can deal with future financial setbacks for 3 full years.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The turnover forecast is adequately substantiated and in line with market potential.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The cash flow from factual business activities must be positive for 3 full years.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Reliability of the organisation", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Are your organisation and the natural persons and legal entities involved in your organisation, reliable? The IND examines this in the application for recognition. You are considered unreliable in the following situations:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Your organisation, or the natural persons and legal entities involved in your organisation, became insolvent 3 times in the year preceding the application.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The tax authorities gave your organisation a negligence penalty in the 4 years before the application.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your organisation got 3 or more penalties in the 4 years before the application. These are the penalties concerned:", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "penalty under the Aliens Act (Vw);", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "penalty under the Foreign Nationals (Employment) Act (Wav); and", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "penalty under the Minimum Wage and Minimum Holiday Allowance Act (WML).", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The IND withdrew your recognition as a sponsor in the 5 years before this new application.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Additional requirements per category", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Extra requirements to become a recognised sponsor apply to the categories research, study and exchange.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Show detai