Your school provides study programmes in the context of the Cultural Policy Act (Special Purpose Funding) (in Dutch: Wet op het specifiek cultuurbeleid).", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Secondary schools", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Your school provides secondary education as referred to in the Secondary Education Act (in Dutch: Wet op het voortgezet onderwijs or WVO).", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Vocational education schools", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Your school provides vocational education as referred to in the Adult and Vocational Education Act (in Dutch: Wet educatie en beroepsonderwijs or WEB).", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Secondary schools that offer the international baccalaureate diploma programme", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Your school is accredited by the International Baccalaureate Organisation.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your school is part of an international organisation that exchanges students across the world. National committees of this international organisation determine the country of placement. Your school places students in a boarding school.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Requirements for exchange", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "These requirements apply to your au pair agency or exchange organisation.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Your au pair agency is located in the Netherlands. Or in another EU or EEA country.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your au pair agency is registered in the Commercial Register at the Dutch Chamber of Commerce. If this registration is not required by law, then this requirement does not apply.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your au pair agency or exchange organisation has a cultural purpose.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your au pair agency runs an exchange programme that has been approved by the Minister of Asylum and Migration. Read more about the requirements that an exchange programme must meet in", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Exchange Programme 3015(PDF, 315.35 KB)", "type"