er if you have stayed in the Netherlands before. But the IND has ended this residency.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "2. Collect documents", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You need a valid passport to register. The passport needs to be given out by a country from the EU, EEA or Switzerland.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "What other documents you need depend on your situation. Have official foreign documents legalised and translated to Dutch, English, French or German.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You are an employee", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You need 1 of these documents:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "The ''Employer''s declaration'' appendix. This is included with the registration form. Your employer should complete and sign the declaration.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "An employment contract proving that you carry out genuine and effective work in the Netherlands. Read when you carry out genuine and effective work under EU law.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are an entrepreneur", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Proof that your company is entered in the Commercial Register of the Chamber of Commerce.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Proof that you are carrying out genuine and effective work in the Netherlands. Read when you carry out genuine and effective work under EU law. Examples of the proof are for example:", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "a balance sheet or income statement;", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "a monthly overview of operating results; or", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "a declaration or forecast drawn up by an accountant or financial advisor can be submitted.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are a student", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Original proof of registration with an educational institution.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "A self-declaration that you have sufficient funds. Send the ''Declaration of sufficient means of existence'' with your application.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Appendix Declaration on means requirement 7627 (PDF, 147.28 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Proof of your health insurance (insurance card and/or policy).", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You are economically active", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Proof of your health insurance (insurance card and/or policy).", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Documents proving that you have sufficient funds. Read more on sufficient funds for economically inactive Union citizens.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "3. Apply", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You submit the application in writing by post.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "4. Pay for application", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Registering with the IND is free of charge.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "5. Decision on request for registration", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "The decision is positive: You fulfil the requirements to stay in the Netherlands. You will receive an EU registration card.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The decision is negative: You do not fulfil the requirements to stay in the Netherlands. The IND will not register you. You can lodge an objection to the decision.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "6. Collect registration card", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "After registration with the IND, you will receive an EU registration card. You will receive a letter when your registration card is ready at the IND desk. Then you can make an appointment to collect your registration card.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Application form", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Written application forms", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Download the form. Fill in the form and send it by post.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Registration for citizens of the Union 6021 (PDF, 282.99 KB)", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Staying in the Netherlands if you no longer live with an EU family member", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Apply for permanent residence for citizens of the Union", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Verification against EU-law for family members of Union citizens", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Frequently Asked Questions EU", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Living (and working) in the Netherlands for EU citizens 8005 (PDF, 202.15 KB)", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Rules and regulations", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Articles 8.7 and 8.8 Vreemdelingenbesluit (Aliens Decree)", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Articles 8.11 and 8.12 Vreemdelingenbesluit (Aliens Decree)", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "B10/2 Vreemdelingencirculaire (Aliens Act Implementation Guidelines)", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "When is registering with the IND obligatory", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application form", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Your Europe", "type": "Image"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.781568+00', 'Registering with the IND as an EU, EEA or Swiss citizen

Last update: 8 July 2025

Do you have the nationality of a country of the EU, EEA or Switzerland? Then you do not need a residence permit to stay in the Netherlands. Sometimes you do have to register with the IND. Read when you should register with the IND and how you do this.

When is registering with the IND obligatory

Process and costs

Application form

See also

When is registering with the IND obligatory

As a citizen of the EU, EEA or Switzerland, you only have to register with the IND in the following situation: You have stayed in the Netherlands before as a Union citizen. But the IND has ended this residency. In the Personal Records Database (in Dutch: Basisregistratie Personen or BRP) you are registered with code 41. This code means that you do not have the right of residency in the Netherlands.

This may also have consequences for your rights to benefits. Go to the website of the Tax Administration (Belastingdienst) for more information on rights to benefits.

Process and costs

Show details Hide details

1. Check requirements

Check whether you meet the requirements to stay in the Netherlands as a citizen of the EU, EEA or Switzerland. You should only register if you have stayed in the Netherlands before. But the IND has ended this residency.

2. Collect documents

You need a valid passport to register. The passport needs to be given out by a country from the EU, EEA or Switzerland.

What other documents you need depend on your situation. Have official foreign documents legalised and translated to Dutch, English, French or German.

You are an employee

You need 1 of these documents:

The ''Employer''s declaration'' appendix. This is included with the registration form. Your employer should complete and sign the declaration.

An employment contract proving that you carry out genuine and effective work in the Netherlands. Read when you carry out genuine and effective work under EU law.

You are an entrepreneur

Proof that your company is entered in the Commercial Register of the Chamber of Commerce.

Proof that you are carrying out genuine and effective work in the Netherlands. Read when you carry out genuine and effective work under EU law. Examples of the proof are for example:

a balance sheet or income statement;

a monthly overview of operating results; or

a declaration or forecast drawn up by an accountant or financial advisor can be submitted.

You are a student

Original proof of registration with an educational institution.

A self-declaration that you have sufficient funds. Send the ''Declaration of sufficient means of existence'' with your application.

Appendix Declaration on means requirement 7627 (PDF, 147.28 KB)

Proof of your health insurance (insurance card and/or policy).

You are economically active

Proof of your health insurance (insurance card and/or policy).

Documents proving that you have sufficient funds. Read more on sufficient funds for economically inactive Union citizens.

3. Apply

You submit the application in writing by post.

4. Pay for application

Registering with the IND is free of charge.

5. Decision on request for registration

The decision is positive: You fulfil the requirements to stay in the Netherlands. You will receive an EU registration card.

The decision is negative: You do not fulfil the requirements to stay in the Netherlands. The IND will not register you. You can lodge an objection to the decision.

6. Collect registration card

After registration with the IND, you will receive an EU registration card. You will receive a letter when your registration card is ready at the IND desk. Then you can make an appointment to collect your registration card.

Application form

Written application forms

Download the form. Fill in the form and send it by post.

Registration for citizens of the Union 6021 (PDF, 282.99 KB)

