You need a residence permit for medical treatment in the Netherlands. This is also the case if you want to stay in the Netherlands on medical grounds after suspension of your departure for 1 year (Section 64 of the Dutch Aliens Act, in Dutch: Vreemdelingenwet). Find out what the requirements are and how to apply for the residence permit.'),
	('4b00c517-abb9-435c-86aa-d65efa36fb25', 'Residence permit honour-based or domestic violence', 'https://ind.nl/en/residence-permits/other-residence-permits/residence-permit-honour-based-or-domestic-violence', '{"category": "residence-permits/other-residence-permits", "elements": [{"text": "Residence permit honour-based or domestic violence", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Last update: 19 June 2025", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "You do not have a residence permit and you are the victim of, or have been threatened with honour-based violence or domestic violence. As a result the relationship or family bond has ended. You may be able to get a residence permit.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Requirements", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Process and costs", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "Application forms", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "The residence permit", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "See also", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Requirements", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You do not yet have a residence permit. Do you have a residence permit to live with a family member or relative? And are you a victim of violence within the family? Then you can apply for a non-temporary humanitarian residence permit.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You meet the general requirements that apply to everyone.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You do not meet the requirements for a different residence permit.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Requirements honour-based violence", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You have been threatened with honour-based violence in the Netherlands and in the country of origin. Your country of origin is the country of your nationality. Honour-based violence means that your family has threatened you with violence because they say you have damaged the family honour.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The threat is real (genuine) and cannot be removed in the short term.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The threat of honour-ba