	('f44ece92-5326-4b47-b646-b87981525d61', 'Biometrics appointment: photo, signature and fingerprints', 'https://ind.nl/en/after-your-application/biometrics-appointment-photo-signature-and-fingerprints', '{"category": "after-your-application", "elements": [{"text": "Biometrics appointment: photo, signature and fingerprints", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Last update: 12 February 2026", "type": "UncategorizedText"}, {"text": "You have received a letter from the IND. In the letter it says that we require your photo, signature and fingerprints for your residence document. On this page you make an appointment to provide your biometrics.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Have you fled Ukraine and received a letter stating that the IND needs your biometric data? Then make an appointment on the Biometrics Ukraine page. Ви виїхали з України і отримали лист про те, що IND необхідні ваші біометричні дані? Призначте зустріч на сторінці Біометрія України.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "When to make an appointment", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "You can only make an appoint when you have received a letter from the IND. This can be in these situations:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You have submitted an application for a residence permit. And you have received a letter of receipt for this application from the IND.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "You have received a letter from the IND that we need photo, signature and fingerprints to make your residence document.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "When you make an appointment before receiving a letter, your appointment will be cancelled.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Make an appointment", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "At the Desk or Service Point, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints. You can choose which location you want to go to. Providing biometrics is free of charge.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Providing biometrics in Amsterdam, Den Haag, Haarlem, ''s-Hertogenbosch, Zwolle, Enschede or Utrecht", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Would you like to provide biometrics at an IND Desk in Amsterdam, Den Haag, Haarlem, ''s-Hertogenbosch or Zwolle? Or at an Expat Centre in Enschede or Utrecht? Then you can make an appointment at the IND. There, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Make appointment at IND", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Providing biometrics in Maastricht", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you live in the province of Limburg? Then you can make an appointment at the Expat Centre Maastricht. There, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Make appointment in Maastricht", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Providing biometrics in Goes", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Do you live in the province of Zeeland or a municipality in the Brabantse Wal? Then you can make an appointment at the IND Service Point in Goes. There, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Make appointment in Goes", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Biometrics for a child under 1 year", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Is the residence document for a child under 1 year old? Then do not make an appointment for providing biometrics. Please send a passport photo of the child to the using the Appendix Passport photo form. The passport photo must be taken by a photographer. Read more about the requirements for the passport photo.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Appropiate clothing for passport photo", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "We kindly ask you not to wear completely white or light grey clothing. The passport photo is taken against a light grey background. If you wear light clothing, the photo may turn out wrong.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "You may keep your head covered for religious or philosophical reasons. The head covering must not cover your face. We also recommend wearing a plain colored head covering that is not light gray. If your head covering has reflective material or busy patterns, the photo may turn out wrong.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Information about your appointment", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Show details Hide details", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "What to bring to your appointment", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Bring the following documents to your appointment:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Your valid passport or other travel document.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Your appointment code. This code is in the email you receive when you make an appointment online.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Do or did you already have a residence permit in the Netherlands? Or a Foreign Nationals Identity Document (VI) type W or W2? Then bring your (expired) residence document or VI.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Have you lost your residence document or Foreign Nationals Identity Document (VI) type W or W2? Or has it been stolen? Then bring the report of the loss or theft reported to the police.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Appointment for a child age1 or older who was born in the Netherlands", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "As the parent of the child, you must bring the following documents to the appointment:", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Your valid passport or valid residence document.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "The child''s valid passport, or the (copy of) birth certificate, or the (copy of) registration of the child in the Personal Records Database (in Dutch: Basisregistratie Personen or BRP) at the municipality.", "type": "ListItem"}, {"text": "Reschedule or cancel an appointment", "type": "Title"}, {"text": "Have you made an appointment, but are you unable to attend? It is not possible to reschedule your appointment. There is a link in the email with the appointment confirmation. Click on the link and cancel your appointment. After that, make a new appointment.", "type": "NarrativeText"}, {"text": "Have you made an appointment for multiple people? You can only cancel the entire appointment and not for just 1 person.", "type": "NarrativeText"}], "fetch_date": "2026-03-02"}', 'webpage', '2026-03-28 16:32:08.725204+00', '2026-03-28 16:25:32.781568+00', 'Biometrics appointment: photo, signature and fingerprints

Last update: 12 February 2026

You have received a letter from the IND. In the letter it says that we require your photo, signature and fingerprints for your residence document. On this page you make an appointment to provide your biometrics.

Have you fled Ukraine and received a letter stating that the IND needs your biometric data? Then make an appointment on the Biometrics Ukraine page. Ви виїхали з України і отримали лист про те, що IND необхідні ваші біометричні дані? Призначте зустріч на сторінці Біометрія України.

When to make an appointment

You can only make an appoint when you have received a letter from the IND. This can be in these situations:

You have submitted an application for a residence permit. And you have received a letter of receipt for this application from the IND.

You have received a letter from the IND that we need photo, signature and fingerprints to make your residence document.

When you make an appointment before receiving a letter, your appointment will be cancelled.

Make an appointment

At the Desk or Service Point, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints. You can choose which location you want to go to. Providing biometrics is free of charge.

Providing biometrics in Amsterdam, Den Haag, Haarlem, ''s-Hertogenbosch, Zwolle, Enschede or Utrecht

Would you like to provide biometrics at an IND Desk in Amsterdam, Den Haag, Haarlem, ''s-Hertogenbosch or Zwolle? Or at an Expat Centre in Enschede or Utrecht? Then you can make an appointment at the IND. There, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints.

Make appointment at IND

Providing biometrics in Maastricht

Do you live in the province of Limburg? Then you can make an appointment at the Expat Centre Maastricht. There, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints.

Make appointment in Maastricht

Providing biometrics in Goes

Do you live in the province of Zeeland or a municipality in the Brabantse Wal? Then you can make an appointment at the IND Service Point in Goes. There, the IND will take a digital passport photo and take your fingerprints.

Make appointment in Goes

Biometrics for a child under 1 year

Is the residence document for a child under 1 year old? Then do not make an appointment for providing biometrics. Please send a passport photo of the child to the using the Appendix Passport photo form. The passport photo must be taken by a photographer. Read more about the requirements for the passport photo.

Appropiate clothing for passport photo

We kindly ask you not to wear completely white or light grey clothing. The passport photo is taken against a light grey background. If you wear light clothing, the photo may turn out wrong.

You may keep your head covered for religious or philosophical reasons. The head covering must not cover your face. We also recommend wearing a plain colored head covering that is not light gray. If your head covering has reflective material or busy patterns, the photo may turn out wrong.

Information about your appointment

Show details Hide details

What to bring to your appointment

Bring the following documents to your appointment:

Your valid passport or other travel document.

Your appointment code. This code is in the email you receive when you make an appointment online.

Do or did you already have a residence permit in the Netherlands? Or a Foreign Nationals Identity Document (VI) type W or W2? Then bring your (expired) residence document or VI.

Have you lost your residence document or Foreign Nationals Identity Document (VI) type W or W2? Or has it been stolen? Then bring the report of the loss or theft reported to the police.

Appointment for a child age1 or older who was born in the Netherlands

As the parent of the child, you must bring the following documents to the appointment:

Your valid passport or valid residence document.

The child''s valid passport, or the (copy of) birth certificate, or the (copy of) registration of the child in the Personal Records Database (in Dutch: Basisregistratie Personen or BRP) at the municipality.

Reschedule or cancel an appointment

Have you made an appointment, but are you unable to attend? It is not possible to reschedule your appointment. There is a link in the email with the appointment confirmation. Click on the link and cancel your appointment. After that, make a new appointment.

Have you made an appointment for multiple people? You can only cancel the entire appointment and not for just 1 person.'),
